[SN]TITLE[SN]
Boko Haram crisis: The 100-year-old who survived in Nigeria

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Ya Ammuna, who says she is 100 year old, is one of the oldest residents of the Dalori camp in northern Nigeria for those who have survived attacks by Islamist group Boko Haram.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
6 January 2016 Last updated at 17:27 GMT
She told the BBC they keys to her house were taken at gunpoint and then the contents looted.
